name: Eagles
summary: The Philadelphia Eagles' 10-game winning streak came to an end in a 36-33 loss to the Washington Commanders. Eagles quarterback Jalen Hurts left the game with a concussion in the first quarter, and the team was unable to overcome his absence. The Eagles had a 14-point lead in the fourth quarter, but the Commanders rallied to score the game-winning touchdown with just over two minutes remaining. The loss drops the Eagles to 13-3 on the season, and they will need to win their final two games to clinch the NFC East title.

name: Panama Canal
summary: Concerns over fees imposed by Panama have prompted former US President Trump to threaten the resumption of US control over the Panama Canal. This move has been met with opposition from Panama's president, who maintains that such a negotiation is "not negotiable." The Panama Canal has strategic significance, and its control has been a point of contention for many years. The canal's importance to global trade and shipping, particularly for the US, has influenced Trump's threats. Moreover, carriers are implementing surcharges for transiting the canal in the coming year. The issue remains unresolved, with Trump's threats being met with resistance from the Panamanian government.
